org.jorlib.io.tspLibReader

Class TSPLibTour

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jorlib.io.tspLibReader.TSPLibTour

  • public class TSPLibTour
extends Object
    Stores the nodes (by their identifier) that are visited in a tour. Tours are cyclic, so an implicit edge exists between the last index and the first.
    Author:
    David Hadka

      • isHamiltonianCycle

        public boolean isHamiltonianCycle(TSPLibInstance problem)
        Returns true if this tour is a Hamiltonian cycle; false otherwise. A Hamiltonian cycle is a path through a graph that visits every node exactly once.
        Parameters:
        problem - the TSPLIB problem instance this tour is a solution for
        Returns:
        true if this tour is a Hamiltonian cycle; false otherwise

      • reverse

        public void reverse(int i,
                    int j)
        Reverses the order in which the nodes are visited between the two specified indices. The first index defines the start of the reverse operation; the second index defines the stopping position. Tours are cyclic, so the reverse operation, when the second index is less than the first, gets wrapped around the end of the array. The indices are inclusive.
        Parameters:
        i - the first index, or starting index
        j - the second index, or stopping index

      • isEquivalent

        public boolean isEquivalent(TSPLibTour other)
        Returns true if this tour is equivalent to the specified tour; false otherwise. Two tours are considered equivalent if they visit the same nodes in the same order. This comparison ignores the direction of the node traversal.
        Parameters:
        other - the tour that is being compared
        Returns:
        true if this tour is equivalent to the specified tour; false otherwise
